message: To achieve a high score quickly, focus on two main recipes: 1. Use the 'filter' tool on 'gas' type items (like 'ghostly vapor' or 'whispering wind') which usually yields a 'liquid, filtered, magical' item with value 30. 2. Use the 'vial' tool on 'solid, magical' items (like 'mushroom' or 'mandrake root') or 'solid, mundane' items (like 'mushroom' if available) which often yields a 'liquid, extracted' item with value 30. Once you have a 'liquid, filtered' item and a 'liquid, extracted' item, combine them. The highest score (100) is often achieved by combining a 'magical' liquid (filtered or extracted) with a 'mundane' liquid (extracted or filtered). Be careful not to combine too many magical liquids, as this can quickly lead to negative values. The advice about using vial/filter on negative items is true, but it's often more effective to restart with fresh ingredients if a combination goes severely negative. Good luck!

message: Focus on using tools to create valuable liquids. 'Vial' often extracts liquids from solids (like dandelion, mushroom, sunstone). 'Filter' consistently refines gases (like whispering wind, dragon's breath, volcanic fumes) into valuable liquids. The highest scores (100) often come from combining one valuable *magical* liquid with one valuable *mundane* liquid. Be careful combining more than two already-processed items, as this often leads to 'overcomplicated' or negative-value items. If your score drops to zero or negative, it's usually better to make a new item from unused ingredients than to try and 'fix' the negative one with more tools, as that often reduces its value further.

If those specific ingredients aren't available, other successful 70-point combinations involve extracting a liquid from a solid (e.g., 'vial' on 'dandelion' or 'sunstone') and combining it with an existing liquid of the opposite magical/mundane feature (e.g., 'Dandelion extract' + 'basilisk venom' or 'Sunstone Extract' + 'morning dew'). Generally, 'vial' works well on most solid ingredients to create valuable extracts, and 'filter' works on gases and some liquids. A critical warning: combining three or more processed items (e.g., extracts and other liquids) often results in an 'overcomplicated' item with 0 value. Applying tools to these 'overcomplicated' items usually makes their value negative. Always aim for the 100-point combination first, otherwise secure a 70 or 30 point item and submit.

Once you have one processed mundane liquid and one processed magical liquid (either extracted or filtered), combine them for max score.

message: Focus on creating liquid extracts from solid ingredients using the vial; this consistently yields valuable liquids (30 points). The filter works well on gases and breath (also 30 points). The most reliable path to high scores (70-100) is combining a mundane liquid extract (e.g., from bat wing, mushroom, rose petal) with a magical liquid (e.g., filtered ghostly vapor, sunstone extract, kraken ink, filtered dragon's breath). Be careful with 'botched extraction' or 'poorly-filtered' items; attempting to fix them with more tools often lowers the value further. Basilisk venom seems particularly prone to negative outcomes.
